############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Let [`x`] represent the original price of the shirt. Since [`20\%`] is removed to bring the cost down to [`\$51\text{,}`] we can set up the equation:

[```\newcommand{\pinover}[2]{\overset{\overset{\mathrm{\ #2\ }}{|}}{\strut #1 \strut}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\pinover{x}{original}\pinover{-}{minus}\pinover{0.20}{20\%}\pinover{\cdot}{of}\pinover{x}{original}\amp\pinover{=}{is}\pinover{51}{\$51}
\end{aligned}
```]

This equation's solution will be the original price of the shirt, but for now we do not need to solve the equation.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

